<p><strong>Q: Who are the authors of Statistics: 4th Edition?</strong>
<strong>A:</strong> David S. Freedman, Robert Pisani, and Roger Purves</p>
<p><strong>Q: What is the purpose of Statistics: 4th Edition?</strong>
<strong>A:</strong> To provide a comprehensive introduction to statistics for students in the social and natural sciences. The text emphasizes the importance of understanding statistical concepts and how to apply them to real-world data.</p>
<p><strong>Q: What are the key features of Statistics: 4th Edition?</strong>
<strong>A:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Clear and concise writing style</li>
<li>Extensive use of examples and real-world applications</li>
<li>Emphasis on statistical thinking and reasoning</li>
<li>Coverage of both descriptive and inferential statistics</li>
<li>Chapter summaries, practice exercises, and review questions</li>
</ul>
